&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PALS Officer&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Band 5 - Full Time (37.5 hours) - Permanent&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Monday – Friday 08:00-16:00&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Patient Advice and Liaison Service is offering an opportunity for an enthusiastic person to join their team at the Royal Surrey NHS Foundation Trust in Guildford.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post is an exciting opportunity to work with in a team striving to improve patient experience. You will be working in a small team to deliver a patient centred service to patients, relatives and carers who raise healthcare related concerns and enquiries; therefore excellent communication and negotiation skills are essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Previous NHS experience of a very busy demanding department with the ability to demonstrate compassion, empathy and understanding, a flexible “can do” attitude, excellent communication / interpersonal and IT skills. The successful candidate will have strong administration and organisational skills, attention to detail and the ability to work well within a team and on your own.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We encourage applicants to call Tracey Taylor Patient Advice &amp; Liaison Service Manager on 01483 402757 for further information about the role.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview Date : 25th/26th November &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
